<div class="text-content w3-display-container">
    <h3>Roll Checks</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>
        In this game a major mechanic for both roleplay and combat is rolling for 
        the chance to succeed at a certain action to progress a situation or solve a problem.
    </p>
    <p>
        For combat related rolls; all you need are a sufficient number(based of level of target) of 
        successes(d6 dice that results in a number greater than 3) to hit with the move of choice. 
        If you get 5 or more successes(based on level of target as well) you get a critical hit 
        which will do double the base damage. If you get a 6, that counts as 2 successes and if 
        you get two 1â€™s, that gets rid of a success. Here is a table showing the needed # of successes
        in order to hit/crit a certain leveled enemy:						
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Level of Target</th>
            <th># of Successes</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>1-20</td>
            <td>2 (5 to crit)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>21-40</td>
            <td>3 (5 to crit)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>41-50</td>
            <td>4 (7 to crit)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>51+</td>
            <td>5 (9 to crit)</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <p>Here are some of the basic combat related rolls:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Initiative(not an accuracy check/does not need successes): (Initiative)d6</li>
        <li>Melee Attack(Power Attack) Accuracy Roll: (Strength + Fight)d6</li>
        <li>Ranged Attack Accuracy Roll: (Dexterity + Fight)d6</li>
        <li>Staff Attack Accuracy Roll: (Intelligence + Channel)d6</li>
        <li>Spell(Destruction,Restoration,Conjuration) Use Accuracy Roll: (Intelligence+Channel)d6</li>
        <li>Spell(Illusion,Alteration) Use Accuracy Roll: (Wisdom+Channel)d6</li>
        <li>Shout/Power Accuracy Roll: (Constitution + Fight + Channel)d6</li>
        <li>Shield Block/Clash Roll: (Constitution + Clash)d6</li>
        <li>Shield Bash Roll:(Constitution + Fight)d6</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Any perk-related percentage chance roll will simply be one d100 and the roll will 
        be based on the percentage chance(30% = anything between 1 and 30 as a 
        result of a d100 roll will succeed).
    </p>
    <p>
        Any of these roll checks can be changed/decided by the dm as 
        well as any roleplay related rolls can be decided by the dm.				
    </p>
</div>

<div class="text-content w3-display-container">
    <h3>Attribute Mechanics to keep in mind</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>
        For Health, every time you take any form of damage(magical,physical) you add that 
        number to your total damage table, that will affect your current health. If your 
        current health drops to 0, your character dies. Your health does not regenerate 
        during a battle unless you have something that allows health regen or causes health regen.		
    </p>
    <p>
        For Mana/Magicka, every time you successfully cast a spell it will cost you mana
        (that cost will depend on the spell, refer to the Spells tab). 
        If your current mana drops to 0 or below the cost of any spells, you will not be 
        able to cast any more spells until you regen enough mana for that spell.  Your magicka 
        does not regenerate during a battle unless you have something that allows magicka regen or 
        causes magicka regen.
    </p>
    <p>
        For Stamina, every time you do something that uses stamina
        (running in combat, power attacks, etc.) that will cost you a certain amount of stamina:				
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Power Attacks: Attacks you can only do with melee weapons and 
            if they successfully hit they will deal 50% more damage. These attacks cost 
            the weight of your equipped weapon.				
        </li>
        <li>
            Running in Combat: Allows you to travel a distance over 25 ft in one turn. 
            This action cost will depend on the weight of your armor/shield equipped. 
            (See tables in the Movement section)		
        </li>
        <li>
            NO Stamina will regen unless you have an ability/power that will regenerate more stamina.				
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        One other thing to keep in mind, if you exceed your carry cap
        (Items in inventory including equipped armor/sheild unless you have an ability that makes 
        equpped armor weigh 0) you cannot run in combat				
    </p>
